sec.p:
The BLItz Pro Software analysis follows a 1:1 binding model, where:
A+B→kon koff AB \begin{document}$$\displaystyle A+B \underset{k_{\text {off }}}{\stackrel{k_{\text {on }}}{\rightarrow}} A B$$\end{document}
with kon = rate of association or “on-rate” and koff = rate of dissociation or “off-rate”.

Formula for fitting the association (a = slope):


Y=Y0+a(1−e−kobs×t)kobs=kon×[A(M)]+koff
\begin{document}$$\displaystyle \begin{gathered}Y=Y_{0}+a\left(1-e^{\left.-k_{\mathrm{obs}} \times t\right)}\right. \\ k_{\mathrm{obs}}=k_{\mathrm{on}} \times[A(M)]+k_{\mathrm{off}}\end{gathered}$$\end{document}



Formula for fitting the dissociation:


Y=Y0+a×e−koff×t
\begin{document}$$\displaystyle Y=Y_{0}+a \times e^{-k_{\mathrm{off} \times t}}$$\end{document}



Resulting in the equilibrium dissociation constant KD:


KD=koff kon 
\begin{document}$$\displaystyle K_{\mathrm{D}}=\frac{k_{\text {off }}}{k_{\text {on }}}$$\end{document}
